{"key":"processedPost-10111876","value":{"id":10111876,"first":10111770,"last":10112915,"when":1238975318,"utime":"04/06/09 02:48 AM","content":"If you only have one jar, don't do a g2g unless you have a flowhood.&nbsp; <br /><br />Two other points.&nbsp; First is to never sterilize casing layer mixes.&nbsp; Doing so will lead to a higher incidence of contamination.&nbsp; You need to mix it up and pasteurize.&nbsp; <br /><br />Second, Pan cyans either don't fruit from cased grains, or fruit poorly at best.&nbsp; You need to spawn your grains into pasteurized manure, and then when that's fully colonized, apply your pasteurized casing mix on top.<br />RR","title":"Re: Using Glass Jars for Steriliziling Casing Mixture"}}